gd Koninkrijk","Nettlecombe, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Nettlecombe, Somerset, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1065–after 1101":"1065–after 1101","1065–1101":"1065–1101","1070–Female":"1070–Deceased","1090–1179":"1090–1179","1040–1066":"1040–1066","1040–1100":"1040–1100","1090":"1090","1179":"1179","1101":"1101","1100":"1100","1066":"1066","1065":"1065","14 October 1066, killed in the Battle of Hastings":"14 October 1066","1040":"1040","after 1101":"after 1101","1070":"1070","Hastings, Sussex, England":"Hastings, Sussex, England","Raleigh, Devon, England":"Farleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom","Pilton, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Pilton, Devon, England, United Kingdom","Shepton Mallet, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Shepton Mallet, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","Nettlecombe, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Nettlecombe, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"De","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Raleigh","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Raleigh (House) in Pilton (Devon), recorded as <i>Radeleia</i> in 1086 and <i>Rawlegh</i> in 1535. The placename probably derives from Old English <i>rǣge</i> ‘roe deer’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’.","Irish: variant of   Riley  .","History: The English explorer Sir Walter Raleigh (1554–1618) was born in Hayes Barton, Devon, into a family of Devon gentry. He was related to most of the West Country's important families, including that of Sir Francis Drake. His half-brother was the explorer Sir Humphrey Gilbert. In 1578 Raleigh was granted a patent to explore and colonize “unknown lands” in America. In the 1580s he was granted extensive estates in Munster (Ireland), in reward for his suppression of the Desmond Rebellions."],"variants":[{"name":"Raley","meanings":["English: variant of   Raleigh  ."]},{"name":"Rawleigh","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Erwin, Orlo.","English: variant of   Raleigh  , reflecting a common pronunciation."]},{"name":"Riley","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Yorkshire): habitational name chiefly from High Ryley in Accrington (Lancashire) and Riley in Kirkburton, which was in the manor of Wakefield (Yorkshire). In some cases the name may derive from Riley Farm in Eyam (Derbyshire), Royley in Royton (Lancashire), or Rylah in Scarcliffe (Derbyshire). The placenames all come from Old English <i>rȳge</i> ‘rye’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’.","Irish: from <b>Ó Raghailligh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Raghailleach</i>’, Old Irish <i>Roghallach</i>. This is the name of a chieftain family in Cavan, related to the O'Rourkes. In Anglicized form it has also been confused with <b>Ó Raithile</b> found in Munster, usually Anglicized as <b>O'Rahilly</b> or   Rahilly  . See   O'Reilly  ."]}]},{"name":"Walter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, superseding the native Old English form, <i>Wealdhere</i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Walter De Raleigh was born in 1065, in Pilton, Devon, England, United Kingdom, his father, Walter de Raleigh II, was 26 and his mother, Beatrice de Gand, was 25. He had at least 1 son with Beatrice de Malet. He died after 1101, in Shepton Mallet, Somerset, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1065–after 1101":"1065–pärast 1101","1065–1101":"1065–1101","1070–Female":"1070–Surnud","1090–1179":"1090–1179","1040–1066":"1040–1066","1040–1100":"1040–1100","1090":"1090","1179":"1179","1101":"1101","1100":"1100","1066":"1066","1065":"1065","14 October 1066, killed in the Battle of Hastings":"14. oktoober 1066","1040":"1040","after 1101":"pärast 1101","1070":"1070","Hastings, Sussex, England":"Hastings, Sussex, England","Raleigh, Devon, England":"Farleigh, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Pilton, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Pilton, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Shepton Mallet, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Shepton Mallet, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Nettlecombe, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Nettlecombe, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1065–after 1101":"1065–1101 jälkeen","1065–1101":"1065–1101","1070–Female":"1070–Kuollut","1090–1179":"1090–1179","1040–1066":"1040–1066","1040–1100":"1040–1100","1090":"1090","1179":"1179","1101":"1101","1100":"1100","1066":"1066","1065":"1065","14 October 1066, killed in the Battle of Hastings":"14. lokakuuta 1066","1040":"1040","after 1101":"1101 jälkeen","1070":"1070","Hastings, Sussex, England":"Hastings, Sussex, England","Raleigh, Devon, England":"Farleigh, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Pilton, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Pilton, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Shepton Mallet, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Shepton Mallet, Somerset, Englanti, Yh